  "prompt": "If a die is rolled, what is the probability that the number is greater than 4?",
  "response": "When rolling a standard six-sided die, the possible outcomes are the numbers **1, 2, 3, 4, 5,** and **6**. \n\n**Favorable Outcomes:**\nWe're interested in the numbers **greater than 4**, which are:\n- **5**\n- **6**\n\nSo, there are **2 favorable outcomes**.\n\n**Total Possible Outcomes:**\nThere are **6** possible outcomes in total when rolling the die.\n\n**Calculating the Probability:**\nThe probability \\( P \\) of an event is given by the formula:\n\\[\nP = \\frac{\\text{Number of Favorable Outcomes}}{\\text{Total Number of Possible Outcomes}}\n\\]\n\nSubstituting the values:\n\\[\nP = \\frac{2}{6} = \\frac{1}{3}\n\\]\n\n**Conclusion:**\nThe probability of rolling a number greater than 4 on a standard die is **\\(\\frac{1}{3}\\)**, which is approximately **33.33%**.",
